      "arguments": {
        "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json",
        "old_string": "## Execution Flow Summary\\n\\nWhen a request arrives:\\n1. API server calls AdmissionControl.Admit() on the reinvocation handler\\n2. Reinvoker delegates to chainAdmissionHandler.Admit()\\n3. Chain iterates through all registered mutating handlers in order:\\n   - Mutating webhooks (with parallel execution within each webhook)\\n   - Mutating admission policies\\n4. Reinvoker checks if reinvocation is needed, may re-run mutations\\n5. API server calls AdmissionControl.Validate() on the reinvocation handler\\n6. Reinvoker delegates to chainAdmissionHandler.Validate()\\n7. Chain iterates through all registered validating handlers in order:\\n   - Validating webhooks (with optional parallel execution)\\n   - Validating admission policies\\n8. Handlers are ordered by plugin registration, with mutations always before validations\\n\"",
        "new_string": "## Metrics and Decorators\\n\\nThe admission chain is wrapped with decorators:\\n- **WithStepMetrics()** (metrics/metrics.go): Records admission latency, rejections, and errors per plugin\\n- Decorators are applied in inside-out order during ApplyTo()\\n- Metrics decorator wraps individual handlers to instrument admission pipeline\\n\\n## Execution Flow Summary\\n\\nWhen a request arrives at the API server:\\n1. REST handler calls AdmissionControl.Admit() (wrapped by metrics decorator and reinvocation handler)\\n2. Metrics decorator records start time for this step\\n3. Reinvoker delegates to chainAdmissionHandler.Admit()\\n4. Chain iterates through all registered mutating handlers in order:\\n   - NamespaceLifecycle (namespace existence checks)\\n   - MutatingAdmissionPolicy (CEL-based mutation rules)\\n   - MutatingAdmissionWebhook (webhooks that mutate requests)\\n   - Each handler is wrapped by metrics decorator\\n5. Reinvoker checks if reinvocation is needed:\\n   - If any mutating handler set ShouldReinvoke flag, re-run mutations\\n   - Allows webhooks to react to mutations from other webhooks\\n6. REST handler calls AdmissionControl.Validate()\\n7. Metrics decorator records start time for validation step\\n8. Reinvoker delegates to chainAdmissionHandler.Validate()\\n9. Chain iterates through all registered validating handlers in order:\\n   - ValidatingAdmissionPolicy (CEL-based validation rules)\\n   - ValidatingAdmissionWebhook (webhooks that validate requests)\\n   - Each handler is wrapped by metrics decorator\\n10. Metrics decorator records latency and reports success/failure\\n11. Returns to REST handler with admission decision\\n\\n## Key Design Patterns\\n\\n- **Chain of Responsibility**: Multiple handlers form a chain, each can process or reject requests\\n- **Separation of Concerns**: Mutating handlers always run before validating handlers\\n- **Decorator Pattern**: Metrics, decorators wrap handlers to add cross-cutting concerns\\n- **Factory Pattern**: Plugins.Register() and NewFromPlugins() create chains from named plugins\\n- **Reinvocation Policy**: Webhooks can request re-invocation to react to mutations\\n- **Configuration Driven**: Plugins loaded via configuration, not hard-coded\\n\"",
